@user-yw9ys3dz7x Her hearing the aliens implies that she is sensitive to ultrasound. Ultrasound is not detectable by the human (or calibrated) ear. Dolphins, bats and dogs, among many other animals, can hear ultrasound. This also implies that the Xenomorph or any of its 'pre-killing machine stage' versions create ultrasounds. The egg may create ultrasounds to echolocate living beings in the vicinity (bats do this). The Xenomorph itself might do this.

Wendy being sensitive to alien ultrasound may also imply that she will be used (or uses her own weakness) to detect and locate the Xenomorph. Going off the trailer, we can assume the Xenomorph will break free.

Do I think Wendy will ignore everything she hears? No. We have already seen Wendy not ignoring the alien ultrasounds. Whether she ignores all other ultrasounds is hard to say. But that is irrelevant to the story.

